articles.title: A Look Through Time with NASA's Lead Photographer for the James Webb Space Telescope - Science@NASA
articles.description: Nearly two years ago in the early morning hours of Dec. 25, NASA’s James Webb Space Telescope successfully took flight from the jungle-encircled ELA-3 launch complex at Europe’s Spaceport near Kourou, French Guiana. Following a successful deployment in space,…
